


=Leads Status=

==Description==

The Leads Status application defines the possible stages or states of a lead during the qualification process.
These statuses are used in the Leads module to track the sales funnel and organize follow-up efforts.
Typical statuses might include "New", "Contacted", "Qualified", or "Rejected".

==List view==

[../../../../../ujest/snaps/test-screenshots-js-screenshots-crm-leads-status-list-en-us-1-snap.png]

The following fields are displayed in the list view:

- Name: The label of the lead status (e.g., Contacted, Qualified).
- Description: Explanation or criteria for using this status.
- Active: Indicates if the status is currently available for selection.


==Form view==

This view is used to create, view or edit lead status records.

In **create** mode, the form is empty and ready to enter new data.

[../../../../../ujest/snaps/test-screenshots-js-screenshots-crm-leads-status-create-en-us-1-snap.png]

In **view** mode, the fields are filled with the selected record and cannot be edited.

[../../../../../ujest/snaps/test-screenshots-js-screenshots-crm-leads-status-view-10-en-us-1-snap.png]

In **edit** mode, the form is pre-filled and allows modifications.

[../../../../../ujest/snaps/test-screenshots-js-screenshots-crm-leads-status-edit-10-en-us-1-snap.png]

The form includes the following fields:

- Active: Controls whether the status appears in dropdowns.
- Name: Title of the status as shown in the Leads app.
- Description: Internal guidance for when to use this status.


==Delete==

Lead statuses can only be deleted if no leads are currently assigned to them.

Otherwise, the status should be marked as inactive.
